<H3> <TI>   LDP To Set Deadline for No-Confidence Motion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    LDP To Set Deadline for No-Confidence Motion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2106064594 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 20 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2106064594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Concerning the no-confidence motion against the 
Hata cabinet, a top leader of the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP] 
stated on 19 June: "It is hoped that discussions will be held 
on setting a time limit (for submitting the motion)." He seems 
to be concerned with the possibility that if the Social 
Democratic Party [Social Democratic Party of Japan (SDPJ)] 
carries out prolonged consultations with the ruling coalition 
parties without reaching any conclusions before the current Diet 
session comes to an end (on 29 June), it will become impossible 
to submit the no-confidence motion, or even if it were 
submitted, the LDP alone cannot have it adopted. Therefore, in 
setting a time limit, the LDP intends to urge the SDPJ to make 
its decision on going along with the LDP policy. 

</TEXT>

