<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan's Bid for UN Council Seat Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2006053394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0514 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2006053394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Sophism of Hypocrite" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 20 (KCNA) -- The Japanese Foreign 
Minister, Koji Kakizawa, claimed that Japan must be a permanent 
member of the United Nations Security Council with veto power 
and if it got a permanent seat, it would be active to "reflect 
the view of the Asian region and small nations." 
  Commenting on this, NODONG SINMUN today views his remarks as 
a sophism of a hypocrite and an obtrusive rigmarole looking down 
upon Asian countries and small nations. 
  The analyst says: 
  His remarks that Japan will represent the view of the Asian 
region means that it wants to become "the leader" of Asia. Down 
through history, Japan has regarded Asia as the target of its 
aggression and looting. It has considered it to be natural. 
Such a thinking-pattern has been inherited by the present 
Japanese Government authorities. 
  In actuality, Japan is seeking the repetition of its past 
policy of aggression. This is well illustrated by the Japanese 
Government's position on the nuclear issue of the Korean 
peninsula. Japan is watching for a chance of reinvasion, while 
going ahead with the preparation of "emergency security 
legislative arrangements" aimed at sending its Armed Forces to 
the Korean peninsula under the pretext of "countering the 
fictitious nuclear issue" of the DPRK. Japan's military 
aggression on Korea will be the first step toward its comeback 
to Asia for realising its old dream of "the greater East Asia 
coprosperity sphere." 
  How can such a country represent the will of the Asian 
countries? Japan's expression of wish to represent the Asian 
nations is an insult to the Asian nations and people. 
  The Japanese Government expressed the view that "the use of 
nuclear weapons is not contrary to the international law," 
openly favoring the use of nuclear weapons. This indicates that 
Japan will make no scruple of plunging developing and small 
nations into a nuclear holocaust to dominate and plunder them. 
  The Japanese reactionaries must give up their impudent 
ambition and honestly liquidate its past crimes first of all. 

</TEXT>

