<H3> <TI>   Ministry To Open Consulate General for PRC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry To Open Consulate General for PRC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1906094794 Bangkok ZHONG HUA RIBAO in Chinese 15 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> BK1906094794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok ZHONG HUA RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In order to make it more convenient for Chinese in 
southwest China to visit Thailand and following the approval of 
the Chinese Foreign Ministry, the Thai Foreign Ministry decided 
to open a consulate general in Kunming City of Yunnan Province 
on 1 July. The consulate general will be responsible for issuing 
entry visas for Chinese living in Yunnan and nearby provinces so 
that those Chinese who want to travel to Thailand for 
sightseeing or visiting their relatives will not have to travel 
a long distance to apply for a visa from the Thai Embassy in 
Beijing. 
  Silachai Sulai, director of the Chiang Mai Branch of the 
Tourism Authority of Thailand, says that the establishment of 
the Thai consulate general in Kunming will help promote the 
development of a quadrangular economic, cultural, and tourism 
cooperation among Thailand, Burma, Laos, and China. 

</TEXT>

