<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fishermen `Ambushed' in Burmese Water </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fishermen `Ambushed' in Burmese Water </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1706143694 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1706143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to a report from the Public Relations 
Office in Mae Hong Son Province, four Thai fishermen were 
ambushed while illegally fishing in the Pai River inside Burmese 
territory. Police authorities at Nam Phiang Din village rescued 
the only survivor and his long-tail boat. The fisherman, 
identified as Min, was seriously injured and later sent to 
Sisangwan Hospital. Min told the police that he and three 
colleagues of the Thai Yai ethnic group were ambushed by an 
unknown group of armed men at about 2300 on the night of 16 June 
while fishing in the Pai River inside Burma about 10 km from the 
Thai border. Min was the only one aboard the long-tailed boat 
when the ambush took place so he managed to flee the site back 
to Thailand. He believes that his three colleagues were 
probably shot dead. Any attempt to retrieve the bodies of the 
three fishermen will be reported later. 

</TEXT>

