<H3> <TI>   Kobayashi Elected Head of Japan-U.S. Economic Council </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kobayashi Elected Head of Japan-U.S. Economic Council </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2006113894 Tokyo KYODO in English 1123 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2006113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 20 KYODO -- The Japan-U.S. Economic 
Council on Monday [20 June] formally elected Yotaro Kobayashi, 
chairman of Fuji Xerox Co., as the new council chief, council 
officials said Monday. 
  Kobayashi replaces Akio Morita, the former chairman of Sony 
Corp. who is currently undergoing medical treatment after 
suffering a cerebral hemorrhage late last year, the officials 
said. 
  The Council, which is made up of influential Japanese 
business leaders, is a preparatory organization for the annual 
Japan-U.S. business conference which holds debates on trade and 
economic problems between the two countries. The three-day 
conference will be held in Tokyo from July 10. 
  Kobayashi told a press conference after the meeting that the 
Council will create objective standards by which to gauge the 
progress of market-opening measures, and will jointly establish 
a working group for discussions on deregulation by both 
countries at the next conference. 

</TEXT>

