<H3> <TI>   Further Reports on Issues Related to DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reports on Issues Related to DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    LDP Official's `Impression' </H4>

<F P=102> OW2106153394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1515 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2106153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 21 KYODO -- A senior Liberal Democratic 
Party (LDP) official said Tuesday he got the impression that 
North Korea has nuclear weapons during his recent trip to 
Pyongyang. 
  "From the series of talks (with North Korean officials), I 
got an impression that the country possesses nuclear weapons," 
Yoichi Tani told a press conference. 
  Tani, along with former Defense Agency head Taku Yamasaki, 
visited North Korea last week and held talks with North Korean 
officials, including Korean Workers' Party Secretaries Kim 
Yong-son and Hwang Chang-yop. 
  Tani criticized recent remarks by Prime Minister Tsutomu 
Hata, who said he did not believe North Korea has atomic bombs. 
"I don't have the slightest idea why he said such a thing," Tani 
said. 
  Yamasaki, also at the press conference, said North Korea is 
now considering opening the door to its market after solving the 
nuclear issue diplomatically. 

</TEXT>

