<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 21 KYODO -- The House of Councilors' ad 
hoc committee on political reform on Tuesday [21 June] passed 
bills to modify the constituencies for upper house elections. 
  The bills, submitted jointly by the Liberal Democratic 
Party, 
the Social Democratic Party and three other groups, are designed 
to achieve a better balance in representation by adding one seat 
each in four constituencies, while slashing four seats from 
others. 
  There will be no change in the size of the second chamber at 
252 seats. 
  The bills are scheduled to be sent to the House of 
Representatives after their expected passage Wednesday by the 
full upper house. 

</TEXT>

