<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Urges Preparatory Organization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Urges Preparatory Organization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2006061394 Seoul YONHAP in English 0606 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2006061394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 20 (YONHAP) -- The opposition Democratic 
Party (DP) proposed Monday to form a joint standing preparation 
body with the ruling Democratic Liberal Party (DLP) to ensure 
supra-partisan support for an inter-Korean summit. 
  The party's Supreme Council met Monday morning, under the 
presidency of Chairman Yi Ki-taek, and made the proposal after 
agreeing that the inter-Korean summit requires perfect 
preparations since it presents a historic chance to deal with 
various national issues including unification and the nuclear 
problem. 
  Members of the supreme committee also decided to form 
another 
organization inside the party to study details of the summit 
including its agenda. 
  North Korean strongman Kim Il-song, speaking through former 
U.S. President Jimmy Carter, has expressed his desire to meet 
South Korean President Kim Yong-sam for an early summit "at any 
time, any place and without any preconditions." The South's 
leader has welcomed the offer. 
  The opposition party plans to seek an extraordinary session 
of the National Assembly to discuss the North Korean nuclear 
problem and the Seoul-Pyongyang summit. 
  Chairman Yi said before the meeting, "There is no need for 
me 
to visit North Korea ahead of President Kim Yong-sam if the 
inter-Korean summit is pushed ahead with smoothly." 
  North Korea said recently that it would welcome a visit by 
Yi. 

</TEXT>

