<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ranariddh, Hun Sen Visit Indonesia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ranariddh, Hun Sen Visit Indonesia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Greeted by Suharto </H4>

<F P=102> BK2006155694 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0600 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2006155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The president and Mrs. Suharto this morning 
welcomed the Cambodian state guests, namely First Prime Minister 
Norodom Ranariddh and Second Prime Minister Hun Sen, at a 
military ceremony with a 19-gun salute and the national anthems 
of the two countries. After the official ceremony held at the 
Merdeka Palace grounds, President Suharto introduced the two 
Cambodian leaders to the Sixth Development Cabinet ministers and 
other high-ranking Indonesian officials. Shortly after seeing 
the state guests off to the State Guest House, Minister-State 
Secretary Murdiono briefed reporters on the significance of the 
Cambodian guests' visit to Indonesia. 
  [Begin Murdiono recording] Cambodian First Prime Minister 
Prince Ranariddh, who spoke more than the other guests, 
expressed his gratitude for the invitation to visit Indonesia 
and also for Indonesia's role in supporting Cambodia's peace 
process, which led to the establishment of a Cambodia based on 
the new Constitution. Prince Ranariddh also said Indonesia was a 
true friend of the Cambodian people and expressed hope that the 
current visit would further strengthen existing traditional ties 
between the two countries. [end recording] 
  Also present at the ceremony this morning were the vice 
president and Mrs. Sutrisno as well as members of the diplomatic 
corps. The Cambodian state guests are scheduled to lay a wreath 
at Jakarta's Kalibata heroes cemetery this afternoon. 

</TEXT>

