<F P=102>   SK2106091894 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0810 GMT 21 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2106091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent Yi Tong-sik from Beijing] </F>
  [Text] Mrs. Mutsuko Miki, wife of former Japanese Prime 
Minister Miki, said that North Korean President Kim Il-song 
hopes that a North-South summit will be held on 15 August, the 
national liberation anniversary. 
  Mrs. Miki revealed today that during a luncheon for her on 
19 
June, North Korean President Kim Il-song said he wants to hold a 
North-South summit on 15 August and wants the South side to come 
to the North. She noted that Kim Il-song also hoped for the 
achievement of North-South reunification and for the 
establishment of diplomatic relations with Japan at an early 
date, and that he expressed satisfaction with increased 
exchanges with Japan. 
