<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Approves Entry Into WTO Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Approves Entry Into WTO Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2006121394 Seoul YONHAP in English 1149 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2006121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 20 (YONHAP) -- The government, in a 
cabinet meeting on Monday, approved a bill providing for the 
country's joining of the Marrakesh agreement on the 
establishment of a World Trade Organization (WTO). 
  The bill, if approved by the president, will be referred to 
the National Assembly on June 22 for review and approval. 
  A World Trade Organization is to be set up as a permanent 
organization in place of the General Agreement on Tariffs and 
Trade (GATT). 

</TEXT>

