<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reports on Japan-U.S. Auto, Parts Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reports on Japan-U.S. Auto, Parts Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    No Compromise on Autos, Auto Parts </H4>

<F P=102> OW2106134694 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 21 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 7 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2106134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on negotiations on the automobile and 
auto parts sector under the Japan-U.S. economic framework talks, 
a senior official at the Ministry of International Trade and 
Industry [MITI] stated on 20 June: "We cannot make any 
concessions on the point on which we cannot compromise in 
principle." Thus, the official stressed Japan's stand that it 
will not make easy concessions in final consultations on the 
sector, which will start on 24 June to prepare for the 
Japan-U.S. summit talks prior to the July Naples summit (meeting 
of leaders of the seven industrialized nations). 
  It is believed that he reiterated Japan's stance of not 
accepting anything like numerical targets. 

</TEXT>

