<H3> <TI>   MOU on Business Councils Signed With Brunei </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MOU on Business Councils Signed With Brunei </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306104794 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brunei Darussalam may make use of SIRIM, or 
Standards and Industrial Research Institute of Malaysia's, 
facilities and expertise for its industrial products. Its 
minister of industry and primary resources, Pehin Datuk Abdul 
Rahman Taib, said this at a news conference. He said one area 
which Bruneian industries can seek assistance from SIRIM is the 
certification of their products. It will also send personnel to 
SIRIM for training. 
  Earlier, the Bruneian minister and his Malaysian 
counterpart, 
Datuk Sri Rafidah Aziz, witnessed the signing of a memorandum of 
understanding [MOU] between Malaysia and Brunei for the 
establishment of joint business councils between the two 
countries. The councils are aimed at promoting business 
exchanges between the two ASEAN members. 

</TEXT>

