<H3> <TI>   Democratic Union Leader Elbegdorj Retains Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Democratic Union Leader Elbegdorj Retains Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306012694 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1128 GMT 22 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306012694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 22 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- A 
two-day-long conference of the largest public and political 
organization of the Mongolian Democratic Union [name of 
organization as received] has been finished here and heated 
debates being launched but the conference has not resulted in 
great changes in the composition of the leadership. 
  Leader of the Mongolian Democratic Union has remained T. 
Elbegdorj who has been relieved recently of the duties of a 
member of the parliament according to his own request. After 
April's political hunger strike being arranged with the purpose 
of having the government (?resign) according to a number of 
members of the union, the prestige of the organization has 
undermined and there is necessity for renewing the activities of 
the organization. For this aim there has been set up a group 
for renovation of the activities of the Mongolian Democratic 
Union. Apparently the initiative group and its supporters 
failed to have T. Elbegdorj and some other members of the board 
having been viewed to be the major instigators of the hunger 
strike entailing the undermining of the authority of the 
Mongolian Democratic Union, replaced during the work of the 
conference. 

</TEXT>

