<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Editorial Views Diplomats Statement on Reform </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Editorial Views Diplomats Statement on Reform </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2106132994 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2106132994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Station editorial: "A Diplomat in Phnom Penh Says Cambodia, </F>
Which is Facing All Kinds of National and Social Problems, Is in 
Urgent Need of Political Reform"] 
  [Text] Recently, an Asian diplomat, who asked to remain 
anonymous, said that the Cambodian people under the government 
of the two prime ministers are suffering in all aspects due to 
national and social problems. The situation in Cambodia remains 
serious, despite the fact that the UNTAC [UN Transitional 
Authority in Cambodia] spent $2 billion to remedy it. War has 
continued, and nothing has been resolved. More aggressor 
Vietnamese forces have continued to flow into Cambodia. 
Meanwhile, the government with two prime ministers has 
continued to provoke the war, attacking the people and patriotic 
forces. The meager sum of foreign financial aid has been spent 
on the military and war operations. Therefore, no efforts for 
national reconstruction have been made. Even roads in Phnom 
Penh have not been repaired. 
  The economy does not exist because all the money has been 
drained by the war. The people are displaced, thus they have no 
chance to be productive. Some areas that could produce a small 
amount could hardly meet their own need. This is why there are 
no products for export in exchange for foreign currency. The 
officials in the government with two prime ministers are very 
corrupt. 
  This diplomat added that there are currently internal rifts 
within the FUNCINPEC [National United Front for an Independent, 
Neutral Peaceful, and Cooperative Cambodia]. They oppose Prince 
Ranariddh, who has pursued a dictatorial policy and associated 
himself with the Cambodian People's Party [CPC] and especially 
with Hun Sen. Ranariddh does not listen to anyone. He listens 
only to the orders of the United States, France, Australia, and 
particularly the communist Vietnamese through Hun Sen, Sar 
Kheng, and Chea Sim. This is why, although the communist 
Vietnamese have moved the border markers 20 to 30 kilometers 
inside Cambodia, Ranariddh has said nothing. 
  Due to these national and social problems, the people of all 
circles are very worried about the fate of the nation and 
people. Therefore, there have been demands that power be given 
to King Norodom Sihanouk for a few years so that he can settle 
national problems by forming a national salvation government 
with the king as the prime minister and four deputy prime 
ministers, namely, Prince Ranariddh, Hun Sen, (?Sam Rangsi), and 
Khieu Samphan. Only by so doing can the serious national and 
social problems be resolved. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

