<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Ministry Reports Economic Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Ministry Reports Economic Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306101794 Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA in Cambodian 23 
Jun 94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA </F>
<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] The Trade Ministry has reported that Singapore 
is currently Cambodia's most important trade partner. Up to 40 
percent of all imported goods on sale in Cambodian markets are 
from Singapore, which also tops the list of countries bringing 
in major goods such as oil worth around 350 millions dollars 
[currency not further specified]; around 20 millions dollars 
worth of construction materials; and several other millions of 
dollars worth of fabrics, television sets, video machines, and 
other consumer goods. After Singapore, Vietnam brings in about 
20 percent of all goods, the most expensive of which is oil. 
  Apart from these two countries, which hold 60 percent of the 
Cambodian market, there is Thailand. Imported Thai goods 
include construction materials, cement, iron bars, fabrics, 
canned food, and other consumer goods. Imported goods also come 
from Japan, Hong Kong, the PRC, Taiwan, and Malaysia. Cambodian 
goods make up only 10 percent of the market; they include fish, 
meat, vegetables, rice, and a small quantity of handicraft items. 
  According to the Trade Ministry, Cambodia exports only four 
goods: natural rubber, aquatic products, soybean, and sawn wood. 
The latter has been banned by the government since April. Other 
agricultural products have been exported but so far only 
surreptitiously. The authorities therefore are not yet in a 
positon to check the volume of these goods and cannot yet 
include them on the export list. 
  Some economists have predicted that Cambodia could export a 
lot of agricultural products if security is not a major problem 
for farmers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-29978 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas121_i_94006" </HT>


