<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-121 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rural Network Planned for Battambang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rural Network Planned for Battambang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306100394 Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA in Cambodian 23 
Jun 94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA </F>
<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] So Khun, state secretary of the Posts and 
Telecommunications Ministry, recently said that the ministry 
plans to set up the first phase of a rural telecommunications 
network in a number of districts in Battambang Province. 
  The plan is based on an aid of 5 millions German marks from 
the German Government to the Royal Government of Cambodia to 
develop telecommunications in rural areas. The plan is for a 
wireless telecommunications network linking the provincial seat 
and a number of districts. The modern network will be set up in 
densely populated townships for use by the public for an 
appropriate fee. If everything proceeds according to plans, this 
network can be expanded by early 1995 to Mongkolborei District 
in Banteay Meanchey Province. 
  The minister also said that this plan will be implemented by 
the end of this year at the latest. Studies by German 
technicians and those from the ministry were completed a few 
months ago. 

</TEXT>

