<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cambodia Said Debating ASEAN Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cambodia Said Debating ASEAN Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2106141194 Jakarta ANTARA in English 1321 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2106141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta ANTARA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Jakarta, Jun 21 (OANA-ANTARA) -- Cambodia wants 
to learn about reorganizing its armed forces and dealing with 
separatist movements by studying Indonesia's own experiences of 
post-independence restructuring, said Minister/State Secretary 
Murdiono. [passage omitted] 
  On the possibility of Cambodia joining the Association of 
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), Ranariddh said that the issue 
is still being debated. 
  He said that he has received strong support from some ASEAN 
member countries. 
  When asked whether or not Cambodia will attend the ASEAN 
Regional Forum (ARF) meeting in Thailand next year, the prime 
minister simply said that his country has clearly expressed its 
interest in attending the meeting. 
  "We have support from Indonesia and Malaysia. I do not know 
about the other countries such as the Philippines," he said. 
  "But, I should say that we have not yet received an answer 
from the host country (Thailand) about our attending the ARF," 
he added. 
  The Cambodian co-prime ministers and their entourage are 
scheduled to visit the Indonesia Aircraft Industry (IPTN) and 
the Asia-Africa Museum in Bandung on Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

