  [Excerpt] A press statement released by the State 
Secretariat in Jakarta today said that Indonesia and Cambodia 
have agreed to expand their bilateral cooperation in the fields 
of trade, economy, education, and culture. The statement also 
said that an accord on bilateral economic and technical 
cooperation has been signed between the two countries during the 
current visit to Indonesia by the Cambodian co-prime ministers. 
The accord marks a new era in bilateral relations between 
Indonesia and Cambodia because the current bilateral cooperation 
has focussed only on political matters. 
