<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Government Media Ban </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Government Media Ban </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Association Expresses Views </H4>

<F P=102> BK2206134694 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2206134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Central Executive Council members of the 
Indonesian Journalists Association [PWI] said they fully 
understand the government's reasons for revoking the publication 
permits of two magazines, namely, TEMPO, EDITOR and a tabloid 
paper DETIK. 
  In a statement released in Jakarta today, the PWI Central 
Executive Council noted the several warnings issued earlier by 
the government to these three publications. The statement was 
signed by Tony Hadi and Tribuana Said, PWI's secretary general 
and chairman respectively. 
  The PWI Central Executive Council is confident that this 
incident will not cause the active participation of the press in 
national development to slacken and it will not dampen the 
spirit of openness between government officials and the people. 

</TEXT>

