<H3> <TI>   Government Delegation Leaves for UNDP Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Delegation Leaves for UNDP Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2106114194 Vientiane KPL in English 0930 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2106114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, June 20 [date as received] (KPL) -- 
Khamphoui Keoboualapha, deputy prime minister, president of the 
Committee for Planning and Cooperation on June 18 led a 
government delegation of the Lao PDR [Lao People's Democratic 
Republic] to the fifth round table meeting held in Geneva, 
Switzerland, between June 19-21. 
  The Lao PDR itself hosts the meeting which is under the 
sponsorship of the UNDP [United Nations Development Program]. 
The Lao delegation would present to this meeting a development 
strategy of the country from now till the year 2000. The 
strategy covers the development of agro-forestry, industry and 
services, hydro-power construction, education and human 
resources. 
  The Lao Government delegation will brief donor countries and 
international organisations about difficulties facing the 
country and its need in socio-economic development in a hope to 
attract more international fund and investment. 
  UNDP resident representative to Laos Mrs. Ameerah Haq-perera 
would also attend this meeting. 
  After this round table meeting, Khamphoui Keoboualapha and 
his party will pay a good-will visit to France at an invitation 
from the French Government. 

</TEXT>

