<H3> <TI>   Saman Vi-gnaket Meets With Representatives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saman Vi-gnaket Meets With Representatives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306065194 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306065194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Comrade Lieutenant General Saman Vi-gnaket, 
Political Bureau member of the party Central Committee, chairman 
of the National Assembly, and former chief of the Army's General 
Political Department, held a meeting with representatives of all 
Army units from throughout the country on 18 June 1994 in the 
meeting room of the National Defense Ministry. 
  First, Comrade Lt. Gen. Saman Vi-gnaket hailed every service 
of the armed forces for being steadfastly loyal and faithful to 
the nation and the party, consistently enhancing the fine 
traditions of the Lao nation and the Army, resolutely persisting 
in overcoming all difficulties and fulfilling national defense 
and public security maintenance tasks, and striving to 
consolidate themselves to become progressive in all fields. The 
comrade also noted developments in the current international and 
regional situations; the enemy's sinister designs against our 
country; and the party's current policies spelled out in the 
various resolutions adopted by the party, which must be 
profoundly appreciated and strictly implemented by the armed 
forces with a high sense of responsibility. In conclusion, 
Comrade Lt. Gen. Saman Vi-gnaket called on our Army to enhance 
its fine traditions actively; to fulfill the three-duty and 
four-relations tasks [not further specified] exceptionally; and 
to act as a progressive model in all four areas -- firmly 
grasping the party's policy, consistently maintaining the 
revolutionary line, pursuing correct behavioral patterns, and 
maintaining a clean and honest lifestyle. 

</TEXT>

