<F P=103> BK2106115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, June 21 (KPL) -- The `Intersputnik' 
Satellite Station has been transferred from the Ministry of 
Communication, Transport, Post and Construction (MCTPC) to the 
Ministry of Information and Culture for use in expanding radio 
and television system throughout the country. 
  The handing over of the satellite station was held yesterday 
between Bouathong Vongnokham, minister of the MCTPC and Osakan 
Thammatheva, minister of information and culture. 
  Officials concerned said that to implement a plan for the 
expansion of radio and television network throughout the 
country, the two ministries have agreed that this satellite 
station come under the management of the Ministry of Information 
and Culture. 
  Located at km 52 on road 13 north, the Intersputnik 
Satellite 
Station was built for Laos in 1980 by the former Soviet Union 
and used for communication purpose in 1983 under the MCTPC. 

</TEXT>

